  "description": {
    "en": "Often called 'sea cows', these gentle giants slowly graze on underwater plants in warm coastal waters.",
    "zh": "常被称为「海牛」，这些温和的庞然大物在温暖的沿海水域慢慢啃食水下植物。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "West Indian manatees are large, gray, barrel-shaped mammals that can grow up to 4 meters long and weigh over 500 kilograms. They have paddle-like flippers, a flat rounded tail, and small eyes. Their thick, wrinkled skin is often covered with algae, giving them a greenish look.",
      "zh": "西印度海牛是大型灰色桶状的哺乳动物，体长可达4米，体重超过500公斤。它们有桨状的鳍肢、扁平的圆尾和小小的眼睛。它们厚实多皱的皮肤上经常覆盖着藻类，让它们看起来带有绿色。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Manatees are gentle herbivores that spend six to eight hours a day eating seagrass and other water plants. They are usually slow-moving and peaceful, and they must come to the surface to breathe every few minutes. Mother manatees are very caring and stay close to their calves for up to two years.",
      "zh": "海牛是温和的草食动物，每天花六到八个小时吃海草和其他水生植物。它们通常行动缓慢而温和，必须每隔几分钟浮出水面呼吸。海牛妈妈非常爱护幼崽，会在幼崽身边陪伴长达两年。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "West Indian manatees live in warm, shallow coastal waters, rivers, and springs in the southeastern United States, the Caribbean, and Central America. In winter, they gather near warm-water springs and power plant outflows because they cannot survive in cold water. They need water warmer than 20 degrees Celsius to stay healthy.",
      "zh": "西印度海牛生活在美国东南部、加勒比海和中美洲的温暖浅海水域、河流和泉水中。冬天它们会聚集在温泉和发电厂排水口附近，因为它们无法在寒冷的水中生存。它们需要水温高于20摄氏度才能保持健康。"
    }
  },
